result.execSummary:
The defendant George Trevino Rodriguez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Prostitution-Nonmmarital Sexual Intercourse, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 944.30(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Court withheld sentence, but granted defendant credit for Two days time served.

miscConds.notes: All mandatory costs, fees and surcharges during term of probation or civil judgment shall be imposed.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant George Trevino Rodriguez in court with attorney Richard E. Thomey.  Alyssa M. Schaller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Defendant waived rights and pled guilty.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire received and filed.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Parties stipulate to the facts of the complaint as a basis for a guilty plea.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the complaint.  Judgment of Conviction entered. 

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 

Court withheld sentence, but granted defendant credit for TWO DAYS time served in the event that sentence is imposed at a later date.  Court placed defendant on probation for ONE YEAR with the following conditions:
*AODA/ANY TREATMENT DEEMED APPROPRIATE
*ATTEND BENEDICT CENTER PROGRAM
*ALL MANDATORY COSTS, FEES AND SURCHARGES DURING TERM OF PROBATION OR CIVIL JUDGMENT SHALL BE IMPOSED.

Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
State filed motion for portective order. lr

Defendant George Trevino Rodriguez in court with attorney Richard E. Thomey.  Alyssa M. Schaller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Court ordered case adjourned for projected guilty plea in Branch 47; Justice point report received and filed. lr  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for 07-14-2015 at 08:30 am.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION.  Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.  Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant George Trevino Rodriguez in court with attorney Brian Christopher Hagner.  Defendant George Trevino Rodriguez in custody.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  bm

Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for May 20, 2015 at 08:30 am.
